Heat the sesame oil in a wok over a low heat. Add the garlic and lemongrass and fry for 3-5 minutes.Add the vegetable stock and salmon pieces. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to simmer gently for 5-10 minutes, or until the salmon is cooked.Add the noodles and stir well.To serve, pour the broth into a bowl and add the lime wedges.